headline.main: Warships Push Into New Areas To Shell Foe in Southwest Pacific; OUR WARSHIPS GO DEEP INTO ENEMY SEAS

lead_paragraph: ALLIED HEADQUARTERS IN THE SOUTHWEST PACIFIC, Thursday, Dec. 2 -- American light naval craft shelled Gasmata, New Britain, and Madang, New Guinea, during the night and dawn hours of Nov. 29 and 30. It was the first sea bombardment of these enemy strongholds.
abstract: US naval craft shell Jap shore installations and shipping, Gasmata and Madang; Allied planes destroy barges, silence gun positions, damage airdrome, Cape Gloucester area; raid Alexishafen and Kalasa; attack 4 Jap ships north of Talasea; strafe island installations, MacCluer Gulf, and fire Langgur, Kei Islands; map
